A Production subscription is used to host live applications that are accessed by end users. It is the most critical environment and requires high reliability, security, and performance.

For example, a company’s customer-facing website or mobile app backend runs in the Production subscription.

A real-life use case is an online banking system where users perform transactions. Any downtime or failure can have serious consequences, so the production environment must be highly available and secure.

Another example is e-commerce platforms like Amazon, where production systems handle real-time user traffic and transactions.

Strict access control, monitoring, and backup strategies are applied in production environments to ensure stability.

Production subscriptions are the backbone of business operations in the cloud.
